In AOP we have few basic concepts start with
join point
advice
aspect
point cut
target
proxy
weaving

 1. Target = The Main Movie Scene
This is the actual work happening

In movie terms:
The scene being shot (hero fighting, emotional dialogue, etc.)

 Example:
Hero delivering dialogue = Target


 2. Join Point = Every Moment in Shooting

 Any point where something can happen
 In movie terms:

Actor enters
Actor speaks
Camera starts
Scene ends

 All these moments = Join Points


 3. Advice = Extra Actions Added

 What extra thing you want to do

 In movie terms:

Add background music 🎵
Add slow motion
Add lighting effect
Add sound effect

 These are Advices

 Example:

Before hero speaks → play music
After fight → add explosion sound


 4. Pointcut = Choosing Which Scene Gets Effects

 Filter: where to apply advice

 In movie terms:
Director says:
 “Only apply slow motion in fight scenes”

 That selection = Pointcut


 5. Aspect = Full Direction Plan

 Combination of:

What to do (Advice)
Where to do (Pointcut)

In movie terms:
A director’s instruction sheet

 Example:
 “In all fight scenes, add slow motion + loud music”

That whole rule = Aspect


6. Proxy = Assistant Director (Middleman)

 Controls everything before reaching actual scene

 In movie terms:
Assistant director says:

“Wait! Add music first”
“Now shoot scene”
“Add effects after”

 Actor doesn’t know this is happening 

 This middle control = Proxy


 7. Weaving = Final Editing Process

 Combining effects with scenes

 In movie terms:
Editing room where:

Scene + music + effects = final movie

 That merging = Weaving



 8. Cross-Cutting Concerns = Common Movie Effects

 Things used in many scenes

 In movie terms:

Background music
Color grading
Sound effects
Lighting

 These are used everywhere → so handled separately